~ start
Jarn Thorian [#sprite=attribute/neutral]: A pyramid... in the middle of the desert.
Jarn Thorian [#sprite=attribute/neutral]: There must be something inside.
=> END

~ npc_entry
Old Man: Traveler! Stop right there.
Old Man: That pyramid holds three ancient puzzle chambers, sealed long ago by the desert queen herself.
Old Man: But beware... a stone guardian lurks within. Powerful and relentless.
Old Man: Many have entered seeking treasure. Few have returned.
Old Man: Tread carefully, and trust your wits over your strength.
=> END

~ npc_exit
Scholar: Ah... you made it out alive. You've seen him, haven't you? The stone guardian.
Scholar: Long ago, he was a man. A royal guard, sworn to protect the queen with his life.
Scholar: But the day she was taken, he was not at her side. He failed her.
Scholar: They say his grief was so great that the desert gods themselves heard his vow —
Scholar: "I will protect her until the end of time."
Scholar: And so he was reborn in stone, eternal, forever standing watch over her tomb deep within that pyramid.
Scholar: He is not evil. He is... faithful. Cursed by his own devotion.
=> END